# Requirements — Interactive HTML & Presentation Builder

**Project:** wicked-interactive
**Status:** APPROVED — product-owner signoff 2026-05-26 (specify validate gate passed)
**Date:** 2026-05-26
**Archetype:** `specify` (elicit → structure → validate)

---

## 1. Context & Goal

A system that lets **non-technical business users** build and iteratively refine
interactive HTML and presentations almost entirely **in the browser**, with minimal
CLI exposure. The user reviews a rendered draft, selects blocks, attaches plain-language
feedback, clicks **UPDATE**, and the draft regenerates and re-displays live. The user
can navigate the full version history, reset to any prior version, and export the result.

**North-star:** the business user touches the CLI exactly once (to start a session);
everything else happens in the browser.

### Existing substrate (reuse, do not reinvent)
- **wicked-prezzie** — HTML→PPTX conversion, Chrome-headless layout extraction, render,
  theme, per-slide compare-and-refine. Consumed as a **library**, not via subprocess.
- **wicked-bus** — internal event spine (at-least-once delivery, SQLite-backed).
- **wicked-brain** — project knowledge. **wicked-testing** — verification.

### Architecture constraints (decided by multi-model council, 3/3 consensus — 2026-05-26)
These are *given*, formalized as ADRs (see `docs/adr/`). They are constraints on the
solution, not acceptance criteria:
- Stable element anchoring via injected `data-wid` semantic IDs (`{slide}-{role}-{ordinal}`).
- Feedback file `_v{x}.md` = YAML frontmatter + per-element sections (selector, `type`
  enum, instruction, `before` snapshot).
- Determinism-first hybrid regeneration: cheerio DOM surgery for content/style;
  fragment-scoped LLM only for structural changes.
- Live loop: chokidar file-watch → wicked-bus → SSE → iframe `src` swap.
- One long-running local service; wicked-bus as the event spine.

### v1 scope decisions (elicited 2026-05-26)
| # | Decision | Choice |
|---|----------|--------|
| A | v1 build scope | **Generate + instrument** — v1 authors HTML from a brief AND instruments it with `data-wid` |
| B | Reset semantics | **Fork (non-destructive)** — reset copies a version as new head; nothing is destroyed |
| C | Export | **Browser button, in v1** — self-contained HTML + PDF |
| D | LLM in v1 | **LLM in v1** — full hybrid engine ships in v1, gated by ID-preservation invariant (INV-2) |

> **Risk note (council deviation):** v1 is intentionally fatter than the council's
> recommended zero-LLM/zero-export MVP. The council's top risk — the LLM dropping
> `data-wid` IDs during structural edits — is mitigated, not avoided, by INV-2
> (ID-preservation gate) and INV-3 (no collateral change). This risk is accepted by
> the product owner and tracked for the build phase.

